column10: This is the 4th incident in 3 weeks in which drivers exiting Browne Academy have rolled the stop sign while looking up Telegraph rode nearly hitting me on my bike. This time the driver was texting while moving.
A car struck me as I was crossing the exit from Browne Academy. They were looking south down Telegraph and rolled the stop sign. They hit me on the side.
Driver failed to look right as they  ran a stop sign nearly hitting me on my bike.  The crosswalk has a blind spot that driver roll right past.
